  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as financial transactions intended to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - making the funds appear legitimate\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Intentional concealment of criminal proceeds\n- Knowledge that funds originated from illegal activities\n- Transactions designed to hide the money's true source\n\nSpecific criminal statutes provide detailed legal frameworks for prosecuting such activities.",
